Therefore, it is the first time to focus on using cold plasma to fabricate the nanomaterials for ensuring food safety. This review summarizes the characteristics of standard cold plasma systems, principles and progress of cold plasma fabrication of nanomaterials including inorganic nanomaterials, carbon nanomaterials, framework nanomaterials, and biomass nanomaterials (see Table 1
                     ). Food safety applications of nanomaterials fabricated by cold plasma over the years in antimicrobials, detection and removal of contaminants, and food packaging are also summarized (see Fig. 6). Finally, the advantages, limitations, and prospects of cold plasma fabricated nanomaterials for food safety applications are summarized. The relationship between cold plasma, nanomaterials, and food safety applications is shown in Fig. 1
                     .
